text:
(1) Ringling Bros., and Barnum and Bailey's Circus, May 9th and 14th 1927, showing the side show tents. The whole circus occupied three square blocks, from New York Ave. west to Brooklyn Ave., and from Clark-son Ave. north, to Lenox Road.

May 1927.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, from a different angle.

May 1927.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Circus - Ringling Bros. - Barnum & Bailey's - Brooklyn.

(1) Ringling Brothers-Barnum and Bailey's Circus, on the lot extending from New York Ave., to Brooklyn Ave., and from Clarkson Ave., on the North, to Lenox Road. This is the "big tent".

May 9-14, 1927.

(2) The same, from a different angle.

May 9-14, 1927.
